title:
Communication Speaker Appointment Pursuant to my authority under Title 38, MRSA, Ch. 3-A, §577-A, I am pleased to appoint the following to the Coastal and Marine Working Group of the Maine Climate Council, effective immediately;

Representative Lydia Crafts of Newcastle - reappointment;
Representative Tiffany Strout of Harrington.

Communication Please accept this letter as the report of the findings of the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs from its review and evaluation of the following agencies under the State Government Evaluation Act, Title 3, Maine Revised Statutes, chapter 35:

Maine Arts Commission;
Maine Historic Preservation Commission;
Maine Historical Society;
Maine Library Commission;
Maine State Cultural Affairs Council;
Maine State Library;
Maine State Museum; and
Maine State Museum Commission.

Communication Please accept this letter as the report of the findings of the Joint Standing Committee on Transportation from its review and evaluation of the Bureau of Motor Vehicles under the State Government Evaluation Act, Title 3, Maine Revised Statutes, chapter 35.
Maine State Cultural Affairs Council;
Maine State Library;
Maine State Museum; and
Maine State Museum Commission.

Communication Speaker Appointment.Pursuant to my authority under Title 10, MRSA Part 1, Ch. 1-A, §11.4-A2, I am pleased to appoint the following to the Citizen Trade Policy Commission, effective immediately:
The Honorable Morgan Rielly of Westbrook as House Chair of the commission, seat 4;
The Honorable Amanda Collamore of Pittsfield, seat 6.
